title: I cannot install an application. Why? What can I do?
answer:
Possible causes are as follows:

1.​ The Android application package (APK) is corrupted. To solve this problem, contact the APK provider.

2.​ The application has already been installed. To solve this problem, uninstall and reinstall the application.

3.​ The phone's available storage space is insufficient. To solve this problem, delete unnecessary files or uninstall some applications.
